1. Bitcoin spot ETFs had a net outflow of $559 million last week, and only VanEck Bitcoin ETF HODL achieved a weekly net inflow;
2. Ethereum spot ETFs had a weekly net inflow of $1.61 million last week, and only Fidelity Ethereum ETF FETH achieved a weekly net inflow;
3. Bybit has accumulated 446,870 ETH through multiple channels;
4. Singaporean crypto mining machine manufacturer Bgin applied for listing in the United States and plans to raise $50 million;
5. Infini contracts were attacked, and more than $49 million of funds were stolen. Infini officials said they would pay in full;
6. Analysis: Bybit hackers have sold 50,700 ETH, and Bybit purchased 157,600 ETH through multiple brokers;
7. Bybit CEO: Bybit has fully made up for the ETH deficit;
8. RAY may be affected by pump.fun testing the Swap module. 24H decline of nearly 20%;
9. Georgia proposed a second Bitcoin reserve bill, intending to allow the state to invest in Bitcoin without limit;
10. Paidun: Infini theft may be related to private key leakage, and the funds have been exchanged for 17,700 ETH;
11. Infini Lianchuang: There was negligence during the transfer of authority, and the personal private key was not leaked;
12. AI Agent sector fell across the board: swarms fell 26.4%;
13. Bybit: Successfully frozen $42.89 million in stolen funds, thanks to the coordinated efforts of many parties.
